nearby /ˈnɪəˌbaɪ/

1. ADV If something is nearby , it is only a short distance away. 在附近 

例： He might easily have been seen by someone who lived nearby. 他可能很容易被住在附近的人看到。 

例： The helicopter crashed to earth nearby. 直升机坠毁在附近的地面上。 

2. ADJ Nearby is also an adjective. 附近的 [ADJ n] 

例： At a nearby table a man was complaining in a loud voice. 附近的一张餐桌旁一个男子在高声抱怨着。

